Linux Over Windows

Cost-Effectiveness
Free and pen Source: Linux does not require expensive licensing fees, making ait a cost-effective choice for companies
Lower maintenance cost: Linux stable and requires minimal maintenance, reducing operational costs

Performance and Efficiency
Better Resource Utilization: Linux is light weight and consumes very less resources compared to Windows
High Scalability: Linux Efficiently sclaes from small embedded systems to large entrprise data centers without performance degradation

Secure and reliability
Less Vulnerable to malware: Linux has strong user previlege seperation, making it more secure against viuruses and malware
Frequent and Transperant Updates: Regular security patches ensures system stability without needing frequent reboots
High Stability: Linux can run for years wihout crashes, ensuring better uptime and reliability.